******
[7] Brazil (Rio de Janeiro)
Date: Fri 19 Oct 2007
Source: People's Daily Online [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/90001/90782/90880/6286805.html>


Some 55,467 cases of dengue have been registered in Brazil's Rio de
Janeiro state since January [2007], more than in the 4 years prior
put together, according to statistics reported on Thursday [18 Oct
2007] by Brazil's Health Ministry.

The most affected municipality is Rio de Janeiro with 20 378 cases.
"We clearly face an epidemic in the state. There has been a 50
percent growth in the number of cases in 2006, just like the rest of
the country," epidemiologist Edmilson Migowsky said.

The situation could get worse, Migowsky said, because only 1/3 of the
people affected presented defined symptoms and normally only 10
percent of the cases are officially reported.

So far, 18 people have already died [of dengue virus infection] in
Rio de Janeiro state.

--
